        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 12:19AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1219 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northwest of York, or near Kings Mountain State Park, moving
southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kings Mountain, Clover, Crowders Mountain State Park, Kings Mountain
State Park, Grover, South Gastonia, Crowders, Bethany, and Kings
Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
